init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: However, there’s still a problem that they need to face.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It turns out that the asteroids that were supposed to hit the Earth actually missed it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: An unknown, mysterious illness has been appearing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When people get sick, they don’t live long.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Others think it’s from the food supply.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: At a government meeting, the adults realize that they are now dying out.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The children decide to do things differently from their parents.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: No one will be allowed to have more than they need.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Everyone will have clean water to drink.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The children do as they said they would.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Everyone always had everything they needed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Some of them started to eat all the food themselves and didn't share it with anyone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They went to war against the adults.
